modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and transforming OCaml AST nodes using ppx syntax extensions. Operates on core OCaml types such as expressions, patterns, and type declarations. Enables custom pretty-printing and code generation during the compilation phase.

Registers custom syntax transformations for OCaml code, enabling modification of abstract syntax trees during compilation. Works with module types conforming to the `Ocamlapi_ppx__.S.Component` interface. Used to inject or alter code structures in generated or processed OCaml files.
